messages: The child, Eileen, 7 years old, escaped from under the rubble of her house after it was bombed by the occupation army. Her father and brother were martyred, and she suffered fractures and bruises. She dreams of living in peace and receiving treatment.
This child is the only survivor of his family in Gaza.
Under heavy bombardment and shooting from quadcopter drones, the evacuation of the Baptist Hospital [Al-Ahli Arab] that took place yesterday in the north of Gaza.

Seeing is believing, they say. So tell me, Can you believe it?
What you are witnessing in this video is nothing compared to the wide scale of the suffering of Palestinians in Gaza during the ongoing genocide. An avoidable man-made tragedy that is funded by the US and Europe.

Confrontations with the Israeli occupation forces in Beita village, southern Nablus.

من المواجهات بين شبان وقوات الاحتلال في بيتا جنوب نابلس.

Dr. Munir Al Barsh, the Director of Health in Gaza, praised the Algerian delegation for defying the Israeli blockade to enter Gaza and provide medical assistance. Despite attempts by occupation forces to stop them, the delegation's resolve and persistence allowed them to pass through the Egyptian Rafah crossing, offering much-needed relief to the people of Gaza. During the current war, Dr. Al Barsh was detained by occupation forces after refusing to abandon his patients and the hospital. Held for 45 days, he witnessed severe violations, including the removal of bodies from Al-Shifa Hospital by Israeli forces.

Israeli soldiers burning homes in Rafah.

After having been detained and held for 45 days by the occupation forces, Dr. Munir Al Barsh shares his message of utter resolve. Palestinians' commitment to their land, patients, and the wounded despite all difficult circumstances is unwavering.

Massive destruction was caused by the Israeli occupation forces whilst they raided Nour Shams refugee camp in Tulkarm city.

Hassan Al-Fari, a child from North
Gaza, lost his eye during the recent conflict and urgently needs treatment abroad. Meanwhile, his younger brother Jamal is dying before his eyes due to severe malnutrition.
They live in a tent that lacks basic necessities, plagued by rodents and harmful insects, with no proper sanitation.

Martyrs on the ground and patients either dying or crying out not to be abandoned, while hospital beds are dragged through the streets! New horrifying scenes from the evacuation of the Baptist [Al-Ahli Arab] Hospital the day before yesterday in the north of Gaza.

This scene summarizes the hard conditions in the Israeli occupation jails. A Palestinian prisoner just released after 9 months of arrest.

Residents of Gaza City are experiencing a journey of displacement without a destination after occupation forces invaded the eastern and western parts of the city. With nowhere to go, people with children like Kenan have been wandering since early morning, desperately searching for shelter. The continuous bombardment, gunfire, and advancing vehicles have left families in a state of confusion and fear, unsure of their next destination.

Nine Palestinians were killed after the bombing of a home in the north of Nusairat refugee camp.

The moment the Palestinian Mutaz Obayat was released by Israeli occupation forces in a difficult health condition after months of detention in occupation Jails.

الإفراج عن الأسير معزز عبيات من بيت لحم بحالر صحية صعبة بعد اعتقاله عدة أشهر لدى الاحتلال.

أب يودع طفله الشهيد: “إستناني في الجنة يابا”.

Israeli occupation authorities have released Moazaz Obaiat, a Palestinian from Bethlehem, after nine months of detention.

Moazaz’s family was shocked to receive him in such a state, as he is now in poor condition due to the starvation and torture inflicted on thousands of Palestinians by Israel.

An unspoken goal of the war... do you know it?

Palestinian prisoner Moazzaz Obayat has been released after enduring inhumane, deplorable conditions in Al-Naqab (Negev) prison, often likened to Guantanamo due to the severe mistreatment of hostages. Obayat described the prison as a place of unimaginable suffering, with prisoners facing killing, beatings, starvation, destitution, and disease. The prison houses 3,380 prisoners, including women and children.
Abayat expressed hope for the safety and release of his fellow inmates, who continue to endure extreme hunger and neglect.
Attacking children is a war crime.. it needs to stop!!

These leaflets were thrown in Gaza city this morning (10.07.2024):
"To all present in Gaza City,
The safe passages will allow you to pass quickly and without inspection from Gaza City to the shelters in Deir al-Balah and al-Zawayda.
We inform you that the streets of Tariq bin Ziyad and Amr al-Mokhtar are considered safe passages to cross west to Al-Rashid Street (sea) and from there to the south. The streets of Al-Wehda and Khalil al-Wazir are considered safe passages to cross east into the Al-Zaytoon neighborhood and Al-Madeena roundabout, and from there to Salah Al-Din Street south. The city of Gaza will turn into a dangerous battlefield."
Where are people supposed to go when central Gaza is full and targeted?

A scene unfolds in central Gaza as a young boy collects body parts in a bag after an Israeli missile strike on a school that was housing displaced people. The devastating attack has left families and children in utter chaos.

Injuries and martyrs arrive to Al Aqsa hospital following an Israeli air strike that targeted the tents of displaced Palestinians in Al Haker area.

اصابات و شهداء في قصف استهدف خيام النازحين في منطقة الحكر

ثلاثة شهداء و العديد من الجرحى في قصف منزل في دير البلح

Al Jazeera has released footage that shows the moment the Israeli occupation bombed the entrance to Al-Awda school in Abasan al-kabira in the southern part of the Gaza Strip near Khan Younis. Dozens have been killed in the massacre targeting the displaced with many more injured.


صور للجزيرة توثّق اللحظات الأولى للغارة الإسرائيلية على مدخل مدرسة تؤوي نازحين في عبسان شرقي مدينة خان يونس، وتُظهر الصور عددا من النازحين يلعبون كرة القدم داخل ساحة المدرسة قبل القصف

More than 15,000 children have been killed by Israel since the beginning of the genocide war on Gaza in 2023! Over 9 months and the international community is still unable to stop the Israeli killing machine.

هدم منزل قيد الإنشاء من قبل جرافات البلدية في قرية أم طوبا جنوب القدس
A scene showing the difference in the city of Khan Yunis in the south of the Gaza Strip before the war and the destruction and sabotage that befell it during the war..

Residents of Gaza City in the north are holding their ground after leaflets dropped by occupation forces threatened and 'advised' them to evacuate to central Gaza. Central Gaza is already overwhelmed with those displaced from Rafah and other southern areas, with no space or services available to accommodate a large influx from Gaza City. No place in Gaza is safe.

Famine is getting worse in the north of Gaza.

A displaced woman from Gaza City spoke about her experience amongst the displaced people with the poor health conditions they suffer from.
Palestinians inspect the damage following the withdrawal of occupation forces from the Shejaeya neighborhood in Gaza city.

A woman from the south of Gaza speaks to the residents of Gaza City, urging them not to vacate despite the occupation forces' demand. She shares her personal regret and suffering after leaving Gaza City, emphasizing the immense emotional and physical toll of displacement. She recounts how being away from her city and family has led to continuous hardship and a profound sense of loss. Her message is clear: stay in Gaza City, endure the difficulties, and avoid the additional suffering that comes with displacement.

'The occupation is back again calling on the people of northern Gaza to head south.
We're going to go and ask the people of northern Gaza if they're going to leave or continue being resilient and steadfast in the north..

A very cruel scene. All the houses of the Shujaiya neighborhood were completely destroyed by the Israeli occupation forces.
The question remains for the human world, if it exists, where will the inhabitants of this region live?
Two martyrs were recovered from the vicinity of the college on 8th Street. They were targeted while on their way to check on their homes and search for food and gas.

Displaced Palestinians in the north of Gaza have no shelter after they were forcibly displaced several times during the ongoing Israeli aggression against Gaza.

حال النازحين في شمال غزة

With pharmacies in Gaza closed down due to bombardment by the occupation forces, medicines have become scarce and are now being sold by street vendors. This shift has made access to essential medications difficult and unreliable, forcing residents to rely on informal and unregulated sources for their medical needs.

Moazzaz Obayat, a Palestinian prisoner recently released from Al-Nagab (Negev) prison, shares his ongoing trauma during an interview from his hospital bed. Obayat, who endured severe mistreatment and beatings while detained, expressed his disbelief at not being beaten for the past two days. He speaks about the conditions experienced by Palestinians held without charge or trial in Israeli jails. Obayat recounted the visit by Itamar Ben Gir, Israeli Minister of Security and known terrorist, to the prison, who personally participated in his torture. He calls upon the world to recognize the suffering of Palestinians and the daily violence and inhumanity they endure at the hands of the occupation.

A Palestinian documents the bombing of his family’s home and the martyrdom of a number of his family members in Gaza city.

Mus'ab Awwad, a former Palestinian detainee, shared his traumatic experience from his hospital bed. Arrested in 2020, Awwad was subjected to medical neglect and experiments in Israeli prisons, which resulted in him developing a severe form of cancer (sarcoma) in his leg. This ultimately led to the amputation of his leg below the knee.
